  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "1998-01-27", 
    "text": "Accountability for International Bailouts Act of 1998 - Amends Federal law governing the Department of the Treasury stabilization fund to mandate congressional approval as a prerequisite to any action to incur an obligation or make a guarantee through such fund in excess of $250 million for the purpose of engaging in a coordinated international rescue plan for any foreign entity or foreign government."
